# git-snapshot(1) -- create a snapshot of the changes in a dirty working directory

## SYNOPSIS

`git snapshot` [(`-m`|`--message`) <message>]  
`git snapshot` [(`-h`|`--help`)]  
`git snapshot list`  
`git snapshot clear`  
`git snapshot drop` <snapshot>  
`git snapshot apply` <snapshot>

## DESCRIPTION

Used to record the current state of the working directory without reverting it. The snapshot is stored using git stash prepended with snapshot@{i} to differentiate it and stashes created normally.

## OPTIONS

* `-m`|`--message` <message>:
	Message used when creating the stash entry. This has no effect on the snapshot@{i} part of the label.

* `-h`|`--help`:
	Display git-snapshot man page.

* `list`:
	List all snapshots.

* `clear`:
	Remove all snapshots.

* `drop` <snapshot>:
    Drop an individual snapshot in the form snapshot@{<id>}.

* `apply` <snapshot>:
    Apply a snapshot in the form snapshot@{<id>}.
